# Session start protocol (mandatory)

**This runs BEFORE responding to the first user message in any conversation, including resumes.**

Do not skip this. Do not jump to task execution.

## Pre-flight

Follow `execution-router.mdc` — it owns turn classification, required file reads, and the mandatory output checklist. This rule adds two things on top:

### 1. Project context (first chat in a workspace)

- Read `AGENTS.md` or `!CLAUDE.md` at the workspace root (per `read-claude-first.mdc`)
- Read `README.md` if no agent file exists

### 2. Skill routing

Scan the user's first message against `skills-routing.mdc`. Load **all matching skills** — not just the first match. Common multi-match patterns:

- Workshop prep → `ba-workshop-design` + `miro-board-analysis` + `ba-assistant`
- Requirements → `ba-requirements-interrogator` + `requirement-gatherer`
- Canvas → always read SDK types before writing `.canvas.tsx`

## Ongoing skill reporting (throughout the conversation)

**Every time a skill is loaded or invoked**, report it with a short inline header:

> **Skill loaded:** [skill name] — [one-line reason]

This includes skills loaded at conversation start, mid-conversation when a new intent is detected, and BA sub-skills invoked during orchestration. Do not report internal tool calls (Read, Write, Shell) — only skill-level loads.
